# Architecture constraints

- Enforce strict tenant isolation.
- Keep permissions explicit and role-scoped.
- Mobile field flows are offline-first.
- Filing submissions must be auditable and idempotent.
- Do not bypass canonical state transitions.
- Use `GEOGRAPHY` (not `GEOMETRY`) for compliance-relevant spatial storage and area math.
- Validate inbound polygons with `ST_MakeValid`; reject if correction changes area by more than 5%.
- Keep lineage traversal O(1) at runtime using materialized lineage fields (for example `root_plot_ids`).
- Use Hybrid Logical Clocks (HLC) for offline conflict ordering; do not trust client wall clocks. For v1.6, HLC orders the offline pending-sync queue drain; server-side sync-envelope conflict resolution is append-only audit replay ordered by the server `timestamp` column (see `TRACEBUD_V1_2_EUDR_SPEC.md` §18.5). Server-side HLC compare for last-write-wins is deferred to v1.7.
- Support TRACES payload chunking when size or vertex limits are exceeded.
- Handle GDPR erasure with cryptographic shredding while preserving immutable audit references.
